results.name: a(n) = smallest integer not yet in the sequence with no digits in common with a(n-2); a(0)=0, a(1)=1.
comment: This is not a permutation of the nonnegative integers. E.g. 123456789 and 1023456789 (the smallest pandigital number) are not members.
link: Zak Seidov, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..5000
results.author: _Zak Seidov_ and _Eric Angelini_, Sep 06 2016
